    "body": "I can reproduce the same problem in Chrome browser by using [MDN's example](https://mdn.mozillademos.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/IndexedDB_API/Using_IndexedDB$samples/Full_IndexedDB_example?revision=967085), after some search, I think it is because [Chrome just marked the data as deleted](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/15841828/why-does-empty-indexeddb-still-take-up-space) instead of deleting them immediately, until it has used too much disk space. This totally makes sense because that's how database works.\n"
